# exercises for class,inheritance ,polymorphism,abstraction,encapsulation
q.1)Define the class Point that represents x, y, and z coordinates of 3D coordinate system.  
Now create an object p1 = Point(4, 2, 9) and print it using the statement print(p1).   

class Point:  
    def __init__(self, x, y, z):  
        self.x=x  
        self.y=y  
        self.z=z  
p1 = Point(4, 2, 9)  
print(p1.x,p1.y,p1.z)      

q.2)Improvise the class definition of Point such that any Point object is displayed in the format point : (x, y, z).  

class Point:
    def __init__(self, x, y, z):
        self.x=x
        self.y=y
        self.z=z
    def __str__(self):
        return " point:({0} ,{1} ,{2})".format(self.x, self.y, self.z)    
p1 = Point(4, 2, 9)
print(p1)

